      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can identify a load-bearing wall by looking for its position directly above studs on the first floor or by following a continuous header across the opening where the wall meets the ceiling. Partition walls are typically unsupported at the stud line and rarely have a header spanning above them. Consulting your home's architectural plans or a professional building inspector is the safest way to confirm the structural status before making any modifications.",
